// Vitest Snapshot v1, https://vitest.dev/guide/snapshot.html

exports[`explainer copy snapshots > EXPLAINER_HEADLINE matches snapshot 1`] = `
{
  "title": "Off-band validation for high-assurance environments",
}
`;

exports[`explainer copy snapshots > EXPLAINER_OVERVIEW matches snapshot 1`] = `
{
  "paragraphs": [
    "BEAP is designed to validate messages safely by default. In standard mode, depackaging and validation run on this computer inside an isolated local container with fail-closed behavior and strict validation controls.",
    "This setup adds another layer for higher-risk environments: it deploys an isolated ingestor pod—built from the same code that runs on this computer—onto a Linux VPS you control. A small VPS with root access is enough.",
    "In high-assurance mode, email depackaging happens through the Edge Ingestor. The VPS receives the email content first, depackages it, validates it, and issues a cryptographic validation certificate. Only certified, validated content is then delivered to this computer.",
    "Native BEAP capsules can still be received directly, depending on your security settings. For routes configured to require Edge Ingestor, the local app accepts only capsules with a valid Edge certificate. For routes that allow direct native BEAP, local container validation still runs normally.",
    "High-assurance mode reduces endpoint exposure further. Malformed attachments, zip bombs, complex MIME structures, and high-volume invalid traffic are handled by the VPS before they reach this machine.",
    "Your computer still performs full local validation as a second check. The Edge certificate is a gate, not a replacement. If the certificate is missing where required, invalid, or local validation fails, the message is rejected.",
    "The Edge Ingestor also signs the validated content and its hashes. Any tampering between the VPS and this computer invalidates the certificate.",
    "Local AI analysis remains available to assess phishing, scam, and social-engineering risks before the user interacts with the message. In high-assurance mode, links and attachments should not be opened inside the host environment. Paid tiers can clone the message to a connected sandbox orchestrator, where links and attachments are opened off-band instead of on this computer.",
    "This mode is intended for users and organizations with higher assurance requirements. It does not mean standard BEAP validation is insecure; it adds an additional off-band isolation layer for cases where the stakes are higher.",
  ],
}
`;
